==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metamere
<hw>Met"a*mere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>meta-</ets> + <ets>-mere</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>One
of successive or homodynamous parts in animals and plants; one of a
series of similar parts that follow one another in a vertebrate or
articulate animal, as in an earthworm; a segment; a somite. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Loeven's larva</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metameric</ent>⟦br⟧
